<TEXT>
<P>
 A WALK ACROSS FRANCE by Miles Morland (Fawcett/Columbine: $10; 238 pp.) . At 
45, Morland dealt with his midlife crisis by giving up a lucrative job in 
international finance and making a 553-kilometer trek across France with his 
long-suffering wife. As they hike from Gruissan Plage (near Narbonne) on the 
Mediterranean to Capbreton (near Bayonne) on the Atlantic, Morland savors the 
traditional recipes and life style of Southern France, and endures the 
tasteless food and "boutiquified" communities that are replacing them. His 
expanded journal offers an agreeable armchair journey. 
</P>
