<TEXT>
<P>
 MAGNIFICENT OBSESSIONS: Twenty Remarkable Collectors in Pursuit of Their 
Dreams by Mitch Tuchman, photographs by Peter Brenner (Chronicle: $19.95; 143 
pp., paperback original). During the '80s, the definition of a collectible was 
expanded to encompass anything someone was willing to have around the house in 
large quantities. These brief, up-beat interviews profile 20 people who collect 
a variety of off-beat objects, from Studebakers and carousel horses to aquarium 
figures and toy building sets. Their mania for accumulation seems usually seems 
harmless, but the woman who's amassed thousands of souvenir swizzle sticks may 
lead less sanguine readers to mutter, "Get a life!" 
