<TEXT>
<P>
 DEAD CALM: It's a Deadhead's dream . . . and a Dead-hater's nightmare: Toronto 
producer John Oswald combed through 25 years worth of live recordings of the 
Grateful Dead's "Dark Star" -- perhaps the group's most-loved and most-dreaded 
spacey excursion -- and, using a process he calls Plunderphonics, edited pieces 
of different performances into a seamless, hour-long piece he's titled 
"Grayfolded." And, depending on your leanings, you can either rejoice . . . or 
run and hide: A second volume of the effort is due next year. Steve Hochman 
</P>
