<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: GRANTS: PEPPERDINE RECEIVES $32 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The John C. Tyler Trust has granted Pepperdine University $32.5 million, the 
largest single financial contribution in its 57-year history. 
</P>
<P>
 The university was named the chief beneficiary of the trust after the death of 
Alice Tyler last spring. She was the wife of John Tyler, co-founder of the 
Farmers Insurance Group, who died in 1973. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tylers were active in establishing a $150,000 university-sponsored prize 
for environmentalists as well as a student center on campus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
