<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAIL CALL THANKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * So much has been written and said about the poor service quality of the 
United States Postal Service lately, I'm sure they will appreciate kudos when 
they do something above and beyond the call of duty. 
</P>
<P>
 I have been eagerly awaiting a certified letter . . . running out every day 
when the mail carrier came to see if my letter was there. No luck. The carrier 
took my phone number and said she would call when the letter came in; early one 
recent morning she gave me the good news! Now that is service! Maybe all we 
need to do is ask to get better service! 
</P>
<P>
 MARCY HUBER 
</P>
