<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEMPLE TALK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The photographer missed the significance of the Idfu Temple ("My Best Shot," 
Aug. 21). It is a fine temple to the Egyptian god Horus with its famous granite 
falcon-god guarding the entrance. Horus was the son of Osiris and Isis and had 
a wife named Hathor who made an annual voyage from her temple in Dendora to 
Idfu to reunite with her husband. 
</P>
<P>
 GWEN HEISTAND 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
