<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES WASTES SPACE ON CIGAR SMOKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * What is it with The Times these days? For the second week in a row, I've 
read an article glorifying cigar smoking (the most recent one written by my 
North Hills neighbor Stan Sellers on Sept. 11). 
</P>
<P>
 As an asthmatic and a staunch anti-smoking proponent, I detest stinky stogies 
even more than cigarettes! As a psychologist, I recognize cigar smoking for 
what it really is, just another addiction. 
</P>
<P>
 It is a poor sign of The Times when you decide to devote a half a page to such 
a destructive "hobby." 
</P>
<P>
 I wonder how many people (including kids) reading that article will run out 
and buy stogies because it's "cool." 
</P>
<P>
 Sellers is right about his new hobby. It is breathtaking!  
</P>
<P>
 JAN FERRIS 
</P>
<P>
 North Hills 
</P>
