<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / SPOTLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Thomas Bonk, Bob Cuomo and Emilio Garcia-Ruiz 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 INTRODUCING THE NEW 49ERS 
</P>
<P>
 For what it's worth, the 49 points UCLA allowed against Nebraska, falling just 
four touchdowns shy of the Cornhuskers, ties the most points the Bruins have 
allowed in a game since Terry Donahue took over as head coach in 1977. 
</P>
<P>
 USC defeated UCLA, 49-14, in the 1979 season finale. UCLA finished 5-6 season 
and was seventh in the Pac-10. BACKS AGAINST THE WALL, ITS GUTS AND 
DETERMINATION 
</P>
<P>
 Top Cliche, Revisted, Dept.: From the Associated Press reporter in Dallas, 
covering SMU's victory over New Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
 "Ramon Flanigan, refusing to be denied at the goal line again. . . . " 
</P>
<P>
 Take 'em one at a time, Ramon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
