<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: NEW FEES FOR EXPEDITED PASSPORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beginning Oct. 1, travelers in a hurry will have to pay a $30 fee for 
expedited processing of passport applications. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants who are scheduled to depart in 10 days -- and have the tickets or 
confirmed reservations to prove it -- are eligible for the special service, as 
are travelers who need their passports in order to apply for foreign visas. 
</P>
<P>
 Passports routinely require about two weeks to process -- longer during the 
February-July busy season. In Los Angeles, the passport agency is at the 
Federal Building, 11000 Wilshire Blvd., Suite 13100. The agency has a tape 
recording covering all aspects of passport applications. The number is (310) 
575-7070. 
</P>
