</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A trolley tour called "Tour d'Art" begins Wednesday in New York City, offering 
visitors a new way to see some of the city's cultural institutions, shopping 
areas and neighborhoods. 
</P>
<P>
 The tour, a joint effort of Gray Line New York and the nonprofit Assn. for a 
Better New York, is scheduled to run through Nov. 23.Using trolleys and 
double-decker buses, Tour d'Art will make continuous loops on a route that 
covers Manhattan and includes 31 stops. Passengers may get on and off at any of 
the stops as often as they wish for three full days. 
</P>
