<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOY, 14, FALLS TO HIS DEATH ON HIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 14-year-old Lancaster boy tumbled 50 feet to his death Saturday after he 
lost his footing on a hillside near the California Aqueduct, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, his 14-year-old cousin and his 16-year-old brother were hiking 
near 180th Street West and Lancaster Road just before 3 p.m. when the boy fell 
down a cliff, said Los Angeles County Sheriff's Lt. Daniel Castillo. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies are investigating the incident, Castillo said. 
</P>
