</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Matthew Harding blocked a punt to set up a touchdown, then scored on another 
block as Hawaii, its special teams making up for a struggling offense, stunned 
California, 21-7, on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Longwell, Cal's punter and kicker, missed two field-goal attempts in 
addition to having two punts blocked. 
</P>
<P>
 Two holding penalties, one that negated a 55-yard punt, left Cal facing fourth 
and 47 at its 26 early in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Harding, a junior from San Dimas High, swept in unblocked from the right to 
smother Longwell's punt and Khary Williams picked up the ball and returned it 
20 yards for a touchdown that tied the score, 7-7. 
</P>
<P>
 Longwell had a second punt blocked early in the third quarter when Robby 
Blakeney burst through the middle. Harding scooped up the ball at the Cal 16 
and scored untouched. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawaii (2-1) also sacked California quarterback Dave Barr eight times. 
