<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In nonconference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 3, Santa Barbara 0 -- Vanessa Dahl had five kills and Erin Jones 
added four kills to lead visiting Golden West, 15-5, 15-2, 15-7. Golden West 
improved to 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Bakersfield women's Soccerfest: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 2, Palomar 0; Cypress 3, American River 0 -- Pam Prine scored on a 
header off a corner kick against American River for Cypress (6-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the East Los Angeles men's soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 3, Canada 2 -- Athanasios Koubouras scored two goals and Luciano 
DeLeon added one to lead Orange Coast (2-0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Oxnard men's soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 3, Oxnard 1 -- Kyle Mears scored two goals and D.J. Buckley added 
one to lead Fullerton (2-2-1) in pool play. In an earlier game, Buckley scored 
one goal in the Hornets' 2-1 loss to Hancock. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 1, Southwestern 0 -- Steve Abend scored one goal to lead host 
Golden West (2-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In the finals of the Cuesta water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach 10, Golden West 7 -- John Chomin scored three goals for Golden West 
(8-1) in the championship game. 
