<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; NEWPORT HARBOR WINS VOLLEYBALL TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-ranked Newport Harbor faced its first challenge of the season in the 
finals of the Orange County Volleyball Championships, but the Sailors came back 
to defeat Laguna Beach, 15-17, 17-15, 15-4, Saturday at Edison High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sailors were nearly swept by the third-ranked Artists, who had match point 
in the second game, but were unable to put away two opportunities at the net. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 14-11, in Game 2, the Artists rallied to tie Newport Harbor after 
the Sailors mishandled two sideout chances and Ashley Englander dinked the ball 
into the open back row. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach then got an ace from Lisa Ravensburg to force match point, but 
the Artists could not put away the Sailors, who were able to sideout on Sara 
Fairborn's kill. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor breathed a little easier after Melissa Schutz won a joust at 
the net to tie the score and Schutz then teamed with Jenny Hecker on a block 
for game point. 
</P>
<P>
 Four sideouts later, setter Christy Collisson's attempt to send back an errant 
pass went wide forcing a third game in 1-hour 45-minute match. 
</P>
<P>
 That's when Newport Harbor got into gear behind Misty May, who engineered the 
victory with nine of her match-high 29 kills. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor reached the finals by posting one-sided sweeps over Sunny 
Hills, seventh-ranked Huntington Beach and 10th-ranked Esperanza. 
</P>
<P>
 The Artists had a much tougher road to the championship match. They had to 
defeat three ranked teams in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 They swept No. 4 Calvary Chapel, 15-8, 15-5, and then had to come back against 
sixth-ranked Mater Dei, 6-15, 15-8, 15-6. In the semifinals, Laguna Beach won a 
see-saw match against eighth-ranked Edison, 18-16, 15-10. DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</TEXT>
