<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANDERSON'S BREAKOUT EFFORT KEYS MONTCLAIR PREP ROMP; FOOTBALL: JUNIOR RUNNING 
BACK SCORES FIVE TOUCHDOWNS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL KLEIMAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Running back Akil Anderson rushed for 212 yards in 25 carries and scored five 
touchdowns to lead Montclair Prep to a 48-6 rout of Horizon in a nonleague 
football game Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson had scoring runs of 29, 18, five, four and two yards.It was the first 
big game for the 6-foot, 200-pound junior, who usually stands back and watches 
senior Darrell Dent capture the spotlight. 
</P>
<P>
 Still, Anderson praised the Montclair Prep defense afterward. The Mounties 
limited Horizon to minus-four yards and forced three turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
 "Defense is the center of this team," Anderson said. "When the defense is 
clicking, we can't be stopped." 
</P>
<P>
 Dent, who is being recruited by Notre Dame and Miami, played quarterback and 
wide receiver. He rushed for 46 yards in two carries, caught one pass for 36 
yards and completed his only passing attempt for seven yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mounties (2-0) allowed only three yards passing. Safety Henry Bell 
returned an interception 43 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Horizon's only score came on an 89-yard kickoff return in the first quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
