<P>
GRANZOW PACES FAITH BAPTIST'S 40-6 ROUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quarterback Judd Granzow passed for three touchdowns and rushed for one, 
leading visiting Faith Baptist High to a 40-6 nonleague rout of South Bay 
Lutheran on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Granzow completed 16 of 24 passes for 264 yards as Faith Baptist (2-0) piled 
up 365 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Granzow threw touchdown passes of 35 and 30 yards to Dawayne Lucas. Granzow's 
31-yard pass to Rani Zahr in the first quarter gave Faith Baptist a 6-0 lead. 
The Contenders made it 14-0 on the 35-yard reception by Lucas and a two-point 
conversion run by Granzow. 
</P>
<P>
 Faith Baptist also scored on on a two-yard run by Zahr. 
