<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARA STILL WITHOUT A VICTORY AFTER 41-6 TROUNCING BY ST. MONICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRBY LEE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Clara High scored its first points of the season Saturday night against 
St. Monica. 
</P>
<P>
 The Saints, however, are still without their first victory after being 
trounced, 41-6, in a nonleague game at Santa Monica City College. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Monica jumped to a 12-0 first-quarter lead, but Santa Clara narrowed the 
gap to 12-6 on a one-yard sneak by quarterback Andy Super. 
</P>
<P>
 But Santa Clara (0-2) didn't come any closer. The Mariners scored on five of 
six possessions en route to a 33-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Super completed 10 of 16 passes for 87 yards. Andy Maciel gained 71 yards in 
17 carries and Patrick Davis had six catches for 65 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Monica's Steve Pulley completed six of seven passes for 228 yards and four 
touchdowns. Phil Austin caught touchdown passes of 51, 62 and 73 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
