<HEADLINE>
<P>
STANFORD'S TIGER WOODS WINS COLLEGIATE DEBUT AT INVITATIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. Amateur champion Tiger Woods of Stanford won his collegiate debut, 
shooting a four-under-par 68 Saturday for a three-stroke victory over Oklahoma 
State's Alan Bratton in the 40th Tucker Invitational. 
</P>
<P>
 Woods, a Western High graduate who last month became the youngest player to 
win the U.S. Amateur at age 18, had an eight-under 208 total on New Mexico's 
7,246-yard Championship Course. Bratton closed with a 69. 
</P>
<P>
 Oklahoma State took the team title with an 864 total. Texas was second at 874, 
followed by Arizona State at 879 and Nevada Las Vegas at 881. 
</P>
</TEXT>
