<HEADLINE>
<P>
POWER OUTAGE AFFECTS 3,000 OXNARD HOMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A power outage in the Channel Islands Harbor area of Oxnard kept more than 
3,000 homes in the dark during the early morning hours Saturday, and left 
another 150 residences without power until 3:30 p.m., a Southern California 
Edison spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The outage occurred about 2 a.m. Saturday when a main cable running through 
the area failed, said John Britton, Edison's area manager.Maintenance crews 
arrived almost immediately, but it took several hours to locate the damaged 
cable, Britton said. 
</P>
<P>
 "You're talking miles and miles of cable, and they just have to keep narrowing 
the area down until they find the damage," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Britton speculated that water somehow seeped into the cable causing it to 
short out, but as of late Saturday the cause of the failure was still under 
investigation.  
</P>
<P>
 The main cable was repaired by 9:30 a.m., but about 150 Edison customers along 
Porpoise Way and Peninsula Road remained without power until the cable leading 
into their area was fixed about 3:30, Britton said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
