<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLETA MAN HELD IN CAMARILLO SEXUAL ASSAULTS; CRIME: THE 21-YEAR-OLD IS 
SUSPECTED OF RAPING AND ROBBING TWO FEMALE WORKERS IN A YOGURT SHOP. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man suspected of raping and robbing two teen-agers working at a Camarillo 
yogurt shop was arrested by Ventura County sheriff's deputies and booked into 
County Jail, a Sheriff's Department spokesman said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher Bass, 21, of Goleta was arrested about 7:15 p.m. Friday as he was 
leaving work at Just Bagels in Agoura Hills, said Lt. Craig Husband of the 
Ventura County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Bass is suspected of sexually assaulting the 17- and 19-year-old females at 
gunpoint during an Aug. 29 robbery of a yogurt shop on Carmen Drive in 
Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims reported being attacked by a masked gunman, who, they said, took 
their clothes and threatened them after the assault. 
</P>
<P>
 Because one of the victims saw the suspect before he pulled on a mask, she was 
able to give a detailed description that matched that of a man who robbed as 
many as 14 restaurants and pizza parlors along the Ventura Freeway in Ventura 
and Santa Barbara counties, Husband said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County deputies were assisted by Santa Barbara County sheriff's 
deputies in a two-week investigation that linked the suspect to four robberies 
in the Goleta area and at least three in Thousand Oaks, a Santa Barbara 
Sheriff's Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The break in the case came when detectives from the Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's Department investigating a robbery in Agoura Hills gave Ventura 
County investigators a picture of Bass, Husband said. One of the women was able 
to identify Bass in a photo lineup, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 During the investigation, more than 30 detectives from the Santa Barbara and 
Ventura county departments conducted surveillance, according to Husband. On 
Friday, investigators said they had enough information to arrest Bass at his 
workplace. Employees at the shop said Bass had been a manager at the shop since 
June. 
</P>
<P>
 Bass was booked into the Ventura County Jail on suspicion of robbery and 
multiple counts of sexual assault, a jail spokesman said. Husband said that 
more than $2,000 in cash was found in a search of his residence, and detectives 
are trying to determine whether the cash can be linked to any of the robberies. 
</P>
<P>
 Bass is being held in lieu of $250,000 bail, Husband said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
