<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: PACIFIC GULF PROPERTIES APPOINTS NEW EXECUTIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Angela M. Wixted has been appointed treasurer/controller of Pacific Gulf 
Properties Inc., a Newport Beach real estate investment trust. She was formerly 
controller of O'Donnell Property Services Inc. in Irvine. Before that, Wixted 
was vice president and chief financial officer of SDC Investments Inc. in 
Newport Beach, and a senior accountant with Kenneth Leventhal & Co.'s Newport 
Beach office. 
</P>
<P>
 * Roger Hagie has been appointed to a three-year term on the National Boating 
Safety Advisory Council by Federico Pena, U.S. secretary of transportation. 
Hagie is director of public affairs at Kawasaki Motors Corp. U.S.A. in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 * Roberto C. Medrano has been appointed vice president of sales and marketing 
for Alpha Systems Lab Inc., an Irvine supplier of multimedia, video 
conferencing and surveillance products. Medrano has more than 12 years 
experience in high-technology sales and marketing, including senior management 
positions with Avnet Computer, Sun Microsystems and Daisy Systems Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 * Teresa M. Demarie has been appointed vice president of Executive Horizons 
Inc., a Newport Beach career management and new venture consulting firm. She 
was previously an account executive for Pacific Bell in Los Angeles. Demarie 
has also served as sales training manager for Union Federal Bank in Los Angeles 
and a sales manager for FHP in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * Al Tello has joined the Irvine public relations firm of Laer Pearce & 
Associates as manager of public affairs. He previously served as the executive 
assistant in charge of advising Orange County Supervisor Harriett M. Wieder on 
transportation issues. In addition, Sheri Johnson has been appointed an account 
executive. She was formerly manager of public relations and marketing 
communications for State of the Art Inc., an accounting software developer. 
</P>
<P>
 * Eric F. Rieseberg has been appointed senior vice president, operations, for 
Transitional Hospitals Corp., the long-term critical care subsidiary of Laguna 
Hills-based Community Psychiatric Centers. Rieseberg joins the company from 
Integrated Health Services, a sub-acute health care company based in Owings 
Mills, Md., where he was senior vice president-operations. Before that, he was 
a district vice president for Hospital Corp. of America in Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mark H. Tookey has joined RPM Mortgage as a senior mortgage consultant for 
its Newport Beach office. He was formerly a manager for American Residential 
Mortgage and a senior account executive for Citibank FSB. 
</P>
