</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By David Haldan; Mark Chalon Smith, ; Greg Johnson 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 RANK: Tiny Concordia University in Irvine scores high in the latest collegiate 
rankings from U.S. News & World Report. The school, with 1,500 students, ties 
for fourth among regional liberal arts colleges in the West, up from 19th place 
last year. It tied with LeTourneau University in Longview, Texas. First is 
Evergreen State College in Washington State. . . . Concordia, formerly known as 
Christ College, last year became part of the Concordia University system of 10 
schools operated by the Lutheran Church -- Missouri Synod. 
</P>
<P>
 NEXT? UC Irvine Chancellor Laurel L. Wilkening last week outlined an ambitious 
plan to move the campus into the top 30 nationally ranked research 
universities. (B1) But in the magazine's new rankings released Saturday, 
Berkeley at No. 23 is the only UC campus on the top 25 list of national 
universities. . . .UCI once again finishes in the second grouping of schools 
(26th to 57th), along with UCLA and UC campuses at Davis, San Diego and Santa 
Barbara. No. 1 nationally: Harvard is tops among the national universities, and 
Amherst among the national liberal arts colleges. 
</P>
<P>
 BASEBALL BOYCOTT: As Shawn Atteberysees it, he is a baseball fan first and a 
businessman second . . . So when Major League Baseball canceled the rest of the 
season last week, Attebery cleaned out all of the baseball cards and 
collectibles in his Collectors Only shop on East La Palma Avenue in Anaheim. 
"I'm asking customers not to support Major League Baseball until this madness 
stops," says Attebery. "I'm fed up with the whole charade." 
</P>
<P>
 MARKET MADNESS: So, perhaps you've heard about the big supermarket merger in 
the works in which La Habra-based Food 4 Less would merge its Alpha Beta chain 
with Ralphs Grocery Co. . . . Company officials are not saying yet specifically 
which stores will be directly affected, but industry wags are already 
suggesting possible names for new supermarket combination. Topping the list: 
Ralpha Beta and Food 4 Ralph. 
</P>
</TEXT>
