<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAZARDOUS WASTE IN AUTOMOTIVE BUSINESSES IS WORKSHOP TOPIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A free, bilingual workshop for automotive businesses covering hazardous waste 
and materials is being held Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop will deal with hazardous-waste regulations and reduction, 
employee-safety training and waste management resources that are applicable to 
the automotive industry.Participants will be able to confer with 
representatives from the Los Angeles County Fire Department's Health-Hazardous 
Materials Division, the state's toxics program and other government agencies in 
an informal setting. Concurrent sessions in English and Spanish have been 
scheduled to encourage the attendance of those who may have limited English 
skills. 
</P>
<P>
 Businesses in Bell, Bell Gardens, Commerce, Cudahy, Downey, Huntington Park, 
Los Angeles, Maywood, Montebello, Pico Rivera, South Gate and Vernon may 
participate. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop will be from 4 to 7 p.m. at the Holiday Inn in Montebello. 
Information: (310) 590-4868 or (213) 237-1209. 
</P>
