<TYPE>
<P>
Prep Sports; Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA091894-0403 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 080566 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
September 18, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
City Times; Page 23 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
134 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRIDAY FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ETHAN ALLEN THOMAS JR. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 St. Paul 30, Garfield 6--St. Paul heeded Coach Marijon Ancich's pregame 
warning to play hard to overcome Garfield's size and speed in a rare City 
Section-Southern Section match. 
</P>
<P>
 It was Ancich's 20th victory against City teams in 21 games and the veteran 
coach's 263rd career win. 
</P>
<P>
 Ancich saw running back Elton Gabourel as the key: "We'll see if he can keep 
up with these guys." Gabourel kept up, rushing for 79 yards and a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Garfield posted 127 yards of total offense, but its defense was strong despite 
the lopsided loss, allowing only 172 total yards.  
</P>
<P>
 Garfield's score came with less than three minutes left in the game, when 
backup quarterback Sal Limon connected with Rudy Burruel for a 13-yard 
touchdown pass. 
</P>
<P>
 Next week: Garfield at Huntington Park. ETHAN ALLEN THOMAS JR. 
</P>
