<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY HOME SALES UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nearly 1,100 residential properties were sold in August, an increase of 14.6% 
over the same month in 1993, the San Fernando Valley Assn. of Realtors has 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Of that total, single-family homes captured 972 closed escrows, for the best 
sales tally for the month since August, 1988, and a 16.7% increase over a year 
ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The median resale price of single-family homes that closed escrow last month 
was $175,000, down 10.4% from August, 1993, and 5.4% lower than the median 
reported this July, association statistics indicated. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 8,290 properties were listed for sale on the association's 
computerized Multiple Listing Services, a drop of 34.2% from a year ago when 
12,594 properties were listed for sale. Of that total, 6,383 listings were 
single-family homes and 1,907 were condos. 
</P>
