GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * Plant winter blooming annuals now.Choose from pansies, violas, calendulas, 
Iceland poppies, snapdragons and stock. 
</P>
<P>
 * As the weather cools, you can lower the blade on your lawn mower. 
</P>
<P>
 * Plant winter-blooming cyclamen now. Available in white, pink, rose, lavender 
and red. 
</P>
<P>
 * Add fall leaves to the compost pile to enrich your soil and make plants grow 
better. 
</P>
